Task 2: Inline, Internal, and External CSS
Inline CSS: Styles applied directly on elements using the style attribute.

html:
<p style="color: blue;">This text is blue.</p>

- Internal CSS: Styles defined within a <style> tag in the HTML <head>.

html:
<style>
    p { color: green; }
</style>

- External CSS: Styles defined in an external file and linked in the HTML file.

html:
<link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">

Advantages:
- External: Reusable, centralized styles.
- Internal: Useful for page-specific styles.
- Inline: Fast styling for single elements (use sparingly).